<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-10-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-10-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="586" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d586">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Commander of the Seventh Fleet</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cooke</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to General <persName type="to">Marshall</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-10-05">5 October 1946</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>030210Z. Withdrawal of Marines from bridge, coal mine and train guard
                            duty completed 30 Sept. In each case relief was made by CNA forces.
                            Marines now concentrated Peiping, Tientsin–Taku, Peitaiho–Chinwangtao
                            and Tsingtao. My 040538Z<note n="67" xml:id="d586fn67">Telegram of
                                September 5, not printed.</note> refers.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>